Use the patches in this directory as follows:

For this version of Linux	Use this patch
2.2.18				linux-2.2.18-patch
2.2.19				linux-2.2.19-patch
2.2.20				linux-2.2.19-patch
2.2.21				linux-2.2.19-patch
2.4.18				linux-2.4.18-patch
2.4.19				linux-2.4.18-patch
2.4.20				linux-2.4.20-patch
2.4.21				linux-2.4.21-patch
2.4.26				linux-2.4.26-patch
2.4.26-Debian			debian-2.4.26-patch
2.4.27				linux-2.4.27-patch

Patch Linux using a command like this:
% cd LINUXDIR
% patch -p0 < CLICKDIR/etc/linux-VERSION-patch


WiFi patches
------------

The patch `linux-2.4.20-wifi-patch' adds the Click WiFi extensions to
Linux 2.4.20.  It has three main effects:

1. adds new click_wifi module;
2. modifies airo.c Cisco/Aironet driver to support some Click WiFi extensions;
3. adds the HostAP driver for Prism cards, including Click WiFi modifications.

Apply the patch in the same way as the regular Click patch:
% cd LINUXDIR
% patch -p0 < CLICKDIR/etc/linux-VERSION-wifi-patch

This patch adds new configuration options for the HostAP drivers,
which can be enabled when configuring your kernel.
